entries.title: In Swiss Alps, Some Wonder What a Future Without Snow May Mean
entries.description: An unusually warm winter has forced a rethink about climate change in areas with lower peaks as ski resorts and sporting events face an uncertain future.

entries.title: Your Monday Briefing: A Fatal Plane Crash in Nepal
entries.description: Also a major attack in Ukraine, Japan’s military ambitions and a preview of the Australian Open.

entries.title: Death Toll Rises After Russian Strike Destroys Apartment Block
entries.description: Rescue workers were still digging through the rubble of a residential building in the central Ukrainian city of Dnipro on Sunday, a day after a Russian missile attack.

entries.title: When Being European Parliament President Includes Aiding Police Raids
entries.description: Roberta Metsola, the youngest person to become president of the European Parliament, is seeking to expand the assembly’s role while guiding it through the aftermath of major bribery accusations.

entries.title: Biden’s Goals on Northern Ireland Present Difficult Timetable for Sunak
entries.description: The American president wants Britain’s squabble with Europe over Northern Ireland trade issues settled before the 25th anniversary of the peace accord that ended sectarian violence in the North.

entries.title: Israel Moves Right
entries.description: Israel’s new right-wing government is moving quickly to transform the country.

entries.title: Death Toll Rises After Russian Strike Destroys Apartment Block
entries.description: Rescue workers were still digging through the rubble of a residential building in the central Ukrainian city of Dnipro on Sunday, a day after a Russian missile attack.

entries.title: For Families and Detainees in Russian-Occupied Areas, a Grim Wait
entries.description: After Russia’s retreat from Kherson city, Ukrainians in other occupied areas of the south had expectations of quickly regaining their freedom. But those hopes have been dashed.

entries.title: Plane Crash in Nepal Leaves at Least 33 Dead
entries.description: A twin-engine propeller plane crashed on approach to the city of Pokhara, with 72 people on board.

entries.title: ‘I’m Sorry, We’re From Moscow.’ In Bali, Warring Sides Learn to Cohabitate
entries.description: Thousands of Russians and Ukrainians have fled their homelands for Bali. But even in a tropical paradise, the war is ever-present.

entries.title: Rescuers rush to save people buried in rubble of a building destroyed by a Russian missile.
entries.description: A 15-year-old girl was among the 14 people killed. The search for survivors continues.

entries.title: Britain Says It Will Give Ukraine Tanks, Breaching a Western Taboo
entries.description: Western countries have balked at giving Ukraine tanks and other powerful weapons. As increased spring fighting looms, that seems to be changing.
